@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home — Aspire Demo</PageTitle>

<h1>Aspire Demo</h1>

<p>This app demonstrates <strong>.NET Aspire</strong> — service orchestration, distributed tracing, and PostgreSQL integration.</p>

<h2 class="mt-4">Architecture</h2>
<pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded">
  [Browser]
      │  HTTP
      ▼
  webfrontend  (Blazor Server)
      │  HTTP via service discovery
      ▼
  apiservice   (ASP.NET Core Minimal API — gateway / BFF)
      │  HTTP via service discovery
      ▼
  catalogservice (ASP.NET Core Minimal API — owns the data)
      │  Npgsql + EF Core
      ▼
  postgres     (PostgreSQL in Docker, managed by Aspire)
</pre>

<h2 class="mt-4">Try it out</h2>
<ul>
    <li><a href="products">Products</a> — loads data from CatalogService via ApiService via PostgreSQL</li>
    <li><a href="weather">Weather</a> — loads random data directly from ApiService</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="mt-4">Open the Aspire Dashboard</h2>
<p>
    When you run the AppHost project the Aspire dashboard starts automatically.
    It shows <strong>distributed traces</strong> (see the full Web → ApiService → CatalogService → Postgres span chain),
    <strong>structured logs</strong>, and <strong>metrics</strong> for every service.
</p>
